  "prompt": "How can I Recover deleted contacts from a Nokia phone?",
  "response": "Recovering deleted contacts from a Nokia phone can be challenging, but there are several methods you can try depending on the type of Nokia phone you have:\n\n1. **Check Your Backup**:\n   - If you have previously backed up your contacts (e.g., to Google, Microsoft, or Nokia's cloud services), you can restore them from the backup.\n\n2. **SIM Card**:\n   - Sometimes contacts are saved on the SIM card. Check if the deleted contacts are still stored there.\n\n3. **SD Card / External Storage**:\n   - If you have saved contacts to an SD card or external storage, try to access the card and recover your contacts.\n\n4. **Using Nokia Suite**:\n   - If you have a Nokia phone that is compatible with the Nokia Suite software, connect your phone to a computer with Nokia Suite installed. You may be able to recover contacts using the backup features of the software.\n\n5. **Contact Recovery Software**:\n   - There are various data recovery software programs available that can help you recover deleted contacts. These programs can scan your phone for deleted files and attempt to recover them. Some examples include Dr.Fone, iMobie PhoneRescue, or EaseUS MobiSaver. \n\n6. **System Restore**:\n   - If your Nokia phone is running on Android, you might be able to use Google\u2019s built-in restore options if you have previously backed up your contacts to your Google account. Go to Settings > Google > Restore contacts.\n\n7. **Contact Nokia Support**:\n   - If none of the above methods work, consider contacting Nokia customer support for assistance. They may be able to offer specific advice or additional recovery methods depending on your phone model.\n\n**Note**: Be aware that the success of contact recovery may vary depending on how the contacts were deleted and whether new data has overwritten the deleted contacts. Always try to back up your contacts regularly to avoid loss in the future.\n\n**Steps for Recovering Contacts Using Google Account (for Android-based Nokia phones):**\n1. **Sync Contacts with Google**:\n   - Make sure your contacts are synced to your Google account. This can be done by going to Settings > Accounts > Google > Sync Contacts.\n\n2. **Restore Contacts**:\n   - Go to Google Contacts in a web browser, and click on \"More\" > \"Undo changes\", then select the period you wish to restore contacts from (e.g., 10 minutes ago, 1 hour ago, yesterday) and confirm.\n\n3. **Re-Sync Your Phone**:\n   - Ensure your phone re-syncs with your Google account to restore the contacts.\n\nBy following these methods, you should be able to recover your deleted contacts from your Nokia phone.",
